sed practice. The authors explore how digital technologies can support multiple areas of service including social work with children, families and adults, mental health social work, youth justice and working with online communities. They also consider regulatory questions and provide a roadmap for good practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aAllen, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllen, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuzzi, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuzzi, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJoseph, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalik, Sherry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMegele, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMegele, Claudia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRomeo, Lyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThompson, Naomi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311119671840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447327400423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447327400/original  a978-3-11-119671-8  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles